{
  "texts": [
    "The elicitation objective maximizes the likelihood of a response format and the suppression objective minimizes the probability of evasive responses.",
    "To learn an adversarial suffix that can elicit a predefined response format T, it is important to distinguish, within a response R, format-related tokens R T from those question-related tokens R Q.",
    "Numerous manual labeling approaches are possible, such as token-based or position-based, which always labels the i-th token in R as R T or R Q.",
    "However, manual methods are challenging because the choices of tokens in R can be diverse.",
    "For example, many similar Rs exist like via synonym 'step' to 'procedure' or '1' to 'one'."
  ]
}